01:04.405 --> 01:06.473
Wish me luck.

01:15.420 --> 01:17.422
It's gonna be okay.

01:19.094 --> 01:21.229
We'll see each other again.
I promise.

01:23.166 --> 01:24.366
I promise.

01:36.982 --> 01:39.418
How long
till we get there?

01:39.452 --> 01:42.922
It's hard to say.
Maybe about 300 more miles.

01:42.990 --> 01:44.857
How long will that take?

01:44.892 --> 01:48.362
Maybe 12 hours,
depending on the road conditions

01:48.396 --> 01:50.365
And if we have to take
any more detours.

01:50.399 --> 01:53.069
Any more detours,
and we'll run out of fuel.

01:53.103 --> 01:55.239
Maybe we should think about
scrounging up some more.

01:55.273 --> 01:56.607
Nope, no more side trips,

01:56.642 --> 01:59.011
Not with the aliens
riding on our tail.

01:59.045 --> 02:03.217
The sooner we get to Charleston,
the sooner we'll be safe.

02:03.251 --> 02:06.254
Dad, I want you
to keep this for me.

02:12.431 --> 02:14.633
Why would you write out
a will, Matt?

02:14.667 --> 02:18.171
Well, everyone's saying we're
not gonna make it to Charleston.

02:18.205 --> 02:19.473
And if I die, I want --

02:19.507 --> 02:20.975
You're not gonna die.

02:21.010 --> 02:22.314
And we're gonna make it
to Charleston.

02:22.315 --> 02:24.550
It's not a question of <i>if.</i>
It's a question of <i>when.</i>

02:25.851 --> 02:28.920
I want you to write that
in your journal.

02:28.954 --> 02:30.122
Okay.

02:30.156 --> 02:31.557
Okay?

02:31.592 --> 02:32.992
Yeah.

02:43.832 --> 02:47.832
